---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';

/** TOS_VERSION in backend/apps/signup/models.py must match `version` below — that is
 *  the string recorded against every ISP who accepts, so it is what we would produce
 *  in a dispute. */
---

<Legal
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms under which Danamo Tech Ltd provides the WIFI.OS billing platform to internet service providers in Kenya."
  version="2026-07-01"
  updated="1 July 2026"
>
  <p>
    These terms govern your use of WIFI.OS, a billing and provisioning platform operated by
    <b>Danamo Tech Ltd</b> ("we", "us"), a company registered in Kenya. "You" means the
    internet service provider that holds a WIFI.OS account.
  </p>

  <h2>1. What we provide</h2>
  <p>
    We provide software that lets you sell internet access, provision your routers, collect
    payments from your customers, and account for that money. We are a software and payment
    aggregation service. We are not an internet service provider, and we do not supply
    bandwidth, hardware, or a licence to operate one.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Collection of your customers' payments</h2>
  <p>This is the most important clause in this document, so it is written plainly.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Payments made by your customers are collected into a Danamo Tech M-Pesa paybill
      account, not into your own account.
    </li>
    <li>
      Each payment is attributed to your ISP in a ledger at the moment it is received. That
      ledger is visible to you at all times.
    </li>
    <li>
      Money attributed to you is <b>held on your behalf</b>. It remains yours. We do not
      lend it, invest it, or use it for our own purposes.
    </li>
    <li>
      You may withdraw your available balance to the settlement account you have registered
      with us, at any time, subject to the minimum payout amount shown in your console.
    </li>
    <li>
      We deduct our fees (clause 3) as visible entries in that ledger, never as silent
      deductions from a payout.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Our fees</h2>
  <p>
    Our fees are published at wifios.co.ke/pricing and shown in your console. As at this
    version: a flat monthly platform fee, a percentage of hotspot sales, and a graduated
    monthly fee per <b>active</b> PPPoE client. Suspended clients are not billed. Your first
    month is free. Any assisted-onboarding fee is optional and will not be charged without
    your agreement.
  </p>
  <p>
    We absorb M-Pesa and bank transaction charges on collections and payouts. We may change
    our fees, but we will give you at least 30 days' notice before a change takes effect,
    and you may close your account within that period without penalty.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Your settlement account</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for the accuracy of the paybill or bank account you register with
    us. We pay where you tell us to pay. Changing that destination requires a verification
    code sent to your registered email address, and your first payout to a new destination
    carries a confirmation code which you must read back to us before further payouts are
    released. These controls exist to protect you, and you agree not to circumvent them.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Your responsibilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Hold every licence and authorisation required to operate as an ISP in Kenya.</li>
    <li>Keep your account credentials secure. You are responsible for actions taken with them.</li>
    <li>Deal fairly with your own customers, and honour the plans you sell them.</li>
    <li>
      Do not use the platform to break the law, to defraud anyone, or to attack the network
      or systems of others.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Your customers' data</h2>
  <p>
    Data about your customers belongs to you. We process it on your behalf in order to run
    the service, under our Privacy Policy and the Data Protection Act, 2019. We do not sell
    it, and we do not use it to market to your customers.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Availability</h2>
  <p>
    We work hard to keep the platform running, but we do not promise it will never be
    unavailable. Where the platform is unreachable, your routers continue to enforce the
    sessions your customers have already paid for.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Suspension</h2>
  <p>
    We may suspend an account that is being used unlawfully or fraudulently, or that puts
    the platform or other ISPs at risk. Where we suspend an account, money already
    attributed to that ISP remains theirs and remains withdrawable, save where it is itself
    the proceeds of fraud.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Ending the agreement</h2>
  <p>
    You may close your account at any time. On closure you may export your clients, plans
    and payment history, and withdraw your remaining balance. We will not hold your data
    hostage to keep your business.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Liability</h2>
  <p>
    We are liable to you for money we have collected on your behalf and failed to account
    for. Beyond that, and to the extent the law allows, our total liability to you in any
    12-month period is limited to the fees you paid us in that period. We are not liable for
    your lost profits or for the acts of third parties, including Safaricom and your
    upstream providers.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of Kenya, and the courts of Kenya have exclusive
    jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>Danamo Tech Ltd, Nairobi, Kenya — hello@wifios.co.ke</p>
</Legal>
